  "text": "Most people have no idea football boots are being flipped for profit every single week. Here's how it actually works. Someone buys a limited Adidas Predator Elite at retail, let's say 200 pounds. Two weeks later, it's listed on StockX for 310 pounds. After fees, that's a clean 80 pound profit in 14 days. The reason it works is simple, Nike, Adidas, and Mizuno release limited colorways in batches of under 500 pairs. They sell out in under 20 minutes. Demand stays high. Supply doesn't come back. That gap is where the profit lives. And right now the market is moving fast, boots retract this week are already up 25 to 40%. This is exactly what we break down inside footy culture HQ every single week. Link in bio.",
